1
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:09,916
[YUTA]
With supplies being limited,

2
00:00:09,916 --> 00:00:12,041
we'll need to add a rule
allowing passage

3
00:00:12,250 --> 00:00:13,625
in and out of the colony.

4
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:17,125
But I can't afford
to let players like Dhruv,

5
00:00:17,333 --> 00:00:19,500
who attack people
indiscriminately,

6
00:00:19,708 --> 00:00:21,250
leave the barriers.

7
00:00:21,583 --> 00:00:24,166
I should wait until the players
like him are eliminated

8
00:00:24,375 --> 00:00:26,166
from the other colonies first.

9
00:00:26,375 --> 00:00:29,041
Communication between colonies
is a must.

10
00:00:29,041 --> 00:00:31,333
There's the two rules
Fushiguro proposed.

11
00:00:31,541 --> 00:00:32,833
A means of communication,

12
00:00:32,833 --> 00:00:34,583
and passage
in and out of the colonies.

13
00:00:34,791 --> 00:00:36,166
So we'll need
four additional rules

14
00:00:36,375 --> 00:00:38,208
to get the situation
under control.

15
00:00:38,458 --> 00:00:41,333
Everyone's still at their
physical and emotional limit

16
00:00:41,541 --> 00:00:42,583
from Shibuya.

17
00:00:43,833 --> 00:00:45,166
Gojo.

18
00:00:45,166 --> 00:00:48,166
I won't let you kill
your best friend twice.

19
00:00:49,291 --> 00:00:51,833
I'll kill Kenjaku myself.

20
00:00:52,041 --> 00:00:54,708
I'll get the 400 points
on my own.

21
00:00:54,916 --> 00:00:57,750
JUJUTSU KAISEN

22
00:01:01,625 --> 00:01:03,416
Okay, you can all come out now.

23
00:01:04,041 --> 00:01:06,041
I think we should continue
making our way north

24
00:01:06,041 --> 00:01:07,583
to the edge of the barrier.

25
00:01:07,791 --> 00:01:08,916
[GIRL] Can you carry me?

26
00:01:09,416 --> 00:01:11,166
[MOTHER]
Just hang in there, sweetheart.

27
00:01:11,166 --> 00:01:13,041
Why don't we take a quick rest?

28
00:01:13,250 --> 00:01:14,291
We're safe here.

29
00:01:14,291 --> 00:01:15,708
This stadium
was being controlled

30
00:01:15,916 --> 00:01:17,458
by the sorcerer I just defeated.

31
00:01:17,458 --> 00:01:20,708
Any player that comes along
will be pretty hesitant to--

32
00:01:20,916 --> 00:01:22,625
-[rumbling]
-[MAN 1] What's that sound?

33
00:01:25,708 --> 00:01:28,041
[YUTA] Quick.
Get into the stadium.

34
00:01:28,041 --> 00:01:29,041
[MAN 2] Let's go!

35
00:01:29,250 --> 00:01:31,291
-[panicked chatter]
-Hurry up.

36
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:34,833
[men panting, whimpering]

37
00:01:35,041 --> 00:01:36,125
[man in blue hoodie screams]

38
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:37,166
[gasps]

39
00:01:38,458 --> 00:01:39,875
Help! Help me!

40
00:01:42,041 --> 00:01:43,041
[grunts]

41
00:01:43,041 --> 00:01:44,416
[♪ intense music playing]

42
00:01:45,875 --> 00:01:48,583
[YUTA]
Wait,
are these cockroaches real?

43
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:50,291
[vomits]

44
00:01:50,500 --> 00:01:51,333
[YUTA]
Damn!

45
00:01:56,875 --> 00:01:59,291
-Rika, knock it down!
-[MAN 1] Hurry!

46
00:02:00,333 --> 00:02:01,750
-[RIKA]
Okay!
-[girl whimpers]

47
00:02:01,958 --> 00:02:02,875
[MAN 1] Run!

48
00:02:05,625 --> 00:02:07,291
♪

49
00:02:15,333 --> 00:02:18,833
-Kogane, is that a player?
-Yes.

50
00:02:19,041 --> 00:02:21,583
That is a player
called Kurourushi.

51
00:02:22,708 --> 00:02:25,583
[YUTA]
So some players
are cursed spirits.

52
00:02:26,166 --> 00:02:29,375
EPISODE 59
SENDAI COLONY

53
00:02:32,458 --> 00:02:34,458
FESTERING LIFE SWORD

54
00:02:36,833 --> 00:02:38,000
[whooshing]

55
00:02:39,166 --> 00:02:40,208
[slashes]

56
00:02:40,583 --> 00:02:41,708
[clangs, thuds]

57
00:02:41,916 --> 00:02:42,750
[grunts]

58
00:02:51,333 --> 00:02:52,333
[grunts]

59
00:02:52,708 --> 00:02:54,250
[YUTA]
I'm being watched.

60
00:02:54,583 --> 00:02:57,416
Likely, it's the other
two players with high points.

61
00:02:57,750 --> 00:03:00,041
[KUROURUSHI]
Why do you interfere?

62
00:03:00,041 --> 00:03:02,333
[YUTA]
Kurourushi is a cursed spirit.

63
00:03:02,541 --> 00:03:04,875
[KUROURUSHI] Why do you kill us?

64
00:03:05,458 --> 00:03:06,833
[YUTA]
I can exorcise it.

65
00:03:07,041 --> 00:03:08,750
I just have to drive
positive energy

66
00:03:08,750 --> 00:03:11,916
from my reverse cursed technique
into its body.

67
00:03:12,583 --> 00:03:14,500
I can ask you the same question.

68
00:03:14,750 --> 00:03:16,083
But...

69
00:03:16,083 --> 00:03:19,666
[KUROURUSHI] Because
I like the taste of iron!

70
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:24,333
[YUTA]
I don't want
those other two players

71
00:03:24,541 --> 00:03:27,166
to know I can use
reverse cursed technique.

72
00:03:27,166 --> 00:03:29,833
Rika's protecting everyone
in the stadium.

73
00:03:30,041 --> 00:03:32,000
So I have to
exorcise Kurourushi

74
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:35,166
without using Rika
or my reverse cursed technique.

75
00:03:38,166 --> 00:03:39,208
[clangs]

76
00:03:40,041 --> 00:03:41,166
[KUROURUSHI] Blinding.

77
00:03:41,166 --> 00:03:42,291
Blinding.

78
00:03:42,500 --> 00:03:43,750
Blinding.

79
00:03:46,291 --> 00:03:47,416
[slashes]

80
00:03:57,708 --> 00:03:58,750
[grunts]

81
00:04:11,875 --> 00:04:13,166
[grunts]

82
00:04:14,875 --> 00:04:15,916
[gasps]

83
00:04:17,041 --> 00:04:18,166
[grunts]

84
00:04:18,583 --> 00:04:19,875
[sword clanging]

85
00:04:20,583 --> 00:04:22,458
[Kurourushi growls]

86
00:04:22,666 --> 00:04:23,750
[slashes]

87
00:04:26,291 --> 00:04:27,416
[coughs]

88
00:04:29,166 --> 00:04:31,458
-[mini Kuros squealing]
-[Yuta groans]

89
00:04:32,208 --> 00:04:33,291
[groans]

90
00:04:34,916 --> 00:04:36,208
[breathing laboriously]

91
00:04:37,583 --> 00:04:38,750
[grunts]

92
00:04:39,291 --> 00:04:40,625
[struggling breaths]

93
00:04:40,833 --> 00:04:42,458
[Kurourushi growls]

94
00:04:43,416 --> 00:04:44,416
[Yuta grunts]

95
00:04:44,708 --> 00:04:46,000
-[bites]
-[Kurourushi gasps]

96
00:04:47,458 --> 00:04:49,208
[wind whooshing]

97
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:51,833
[cracking]

98
00:04:56,583 --> 00:04:59,000
[KOGANE] You have gained
five points for a kill.

99
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,875
[TAKAKO]
I see
that you can use...

100
00:05:01,583 --> 00:05:03,750
-...reverse cursed technique.
-[gasps]

101
00:05:09,625 --> 00:05:10,708
[Yuta grunts]

102
00:05:11,166 --> 00:05:12,208
[YUTA]
What was that?

103
00:05:12,416 --> 00:05:14,000
-A strike?
-[Takako grunts]

104
00:05:15,291 --> 00:05:16,416
[grunts]

105
00:05:19,166 --> 00:05:20,791
[glass shatters]

106
00:05:23,875 --> 00:05:25,458
[YUTA]
My arm is back to normal.

107
00:05:25,666 --> 00:05:27,083
I feel fine.

108
00:05:27,083 --> 00:05:29,708
Her technique probably
manipulates space
.

109
00:05:29,916 --> 00:05:31,416
But I guess
she can't use that space

110
00:05:31,416 --> 00:05:32,958
to crush her opponents.

111
00:05:32,958 --> 00:05:36,000
It seems to create distortions
like a funhouse mirror.

112
00:05:36,583 --> 00:05:38,708
[TAKAKO] You're wondering
about my technique?

113
00:05:38,916 --> 00:05:41,416
It treats the sky as a surface.

114
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,583
Here, let me show you.

115
00:05:44,583 --> 00:05:46,625
[YUTA]
She's revealing her technique.

116
00:05:47,208 --> 00:05:49,416
[TAKAKO]
Hurry up and attack already.

117
00:05:49,875 --> 00:05:51,125
[YUTA] I have to ask.

118
00:05:51,333 --> 00:05:52,583
You're not someone
who's gonna complain

119
00:05:52,583 --> 00:05:54,583
about getting killed, are you?

120
00:05:54,583 --> 00:05:55,875
I mean, I can understand

121
00:05:55,875 --> 00:05:58,333
powerless people
getting desperate for points,

122
00:05:58,541 --> 00:05:59,625
but a strong person like you

123
00:05:59,833 --> 00:06:01,416
can claim points
whenever they want.

124
00:06:02,125 --> 00:06:04,750
So what's your reason
for actively seeking a fight?

125
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,500
[TAKAKO]
This little brat.

126
00:06:06,750 --> 00:06:08,333
Seriously?

127
00:06:08,333 --> 00:06:11,291
Are you modern-day sorcerers
that casual about incarnation?

128
00:06:11,291 --> 00:06:12,750
To us from the old school,

129
00:06:12,958 --> 00:06:15,041
this means coming back
from the dead.

130
00:06:15,250 --> 00:06:17,708
People who lived out
their lives without regrets

131
00:06:17,708 --> 00:06:20,291
wouldn't accept
Kenjaku's offer, would they?

132
00:06:20,708 --> 00:06:22,500
He's really pissing me off.

133
00:06:22,708 --> 00:06:24,125
I like to think
of the Culling Game

134
00:06:24,333 --> 00:06:27,208
as the first step toward
a chance at a second life.

135
00:06:27,416 --> 00:06:30,416
Keep in mind that Kenjaku
set the stage for this.

136
00:06:30,625 --> 00:06:32,000
Anything could happen.

137
00:06:32,208 --> 00:06:34,583
We need to earn points
to prepare ourselves.

138
00:06:34,583 --> 00:06:37,750
I wonder if someone like you
has any friends or lovers.

139
00:06:39,583 --> 00:06:40,625
Huh?

140
00:06:41,291 --> 00:06:42,583
You know what?

141
00:06:42,583 --> 00:06:44,708
Until recently, I didn't
have any friends either.

142
00:06:44,916 --> 00:06:46,208
Not that I feel sorry for you.

143
00:06:46,625 --> 00:06:48,291
[TAKAKO]
Hmm, this feeling.

144
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:51,125
It's like he's hunting
for things that trigger me.

145
00:06:51,833 --> 00:06:54,208
[YUTA] Your pain was caused
thousands of years ago.

146
00:06:54,416 --> 00:06:56,875
The people alive today have
nothing to do with your regrets.

147
00:06:57,083 --> 00:07:00,208
How many have to die
until you finally feel avenged?

148
00:07:00,708 --> 00:07:01,916
Wait just a minute.

149
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:04,583
Are you one of the Fujiwara?

150
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,125
How can anyone
from your bloodline

151
00:07:07,333 --> 00:07:08,750
understand me?

152
00:07:10,875 --> 00:07:12,125
[Yuta grunts]

153
00:07:13,458 --> 00:07:15,333
[Takako grunting]

154
00:07:15,541 --> 00:07:16,875
[Takako growling]

155
00:07:19,041 --> 00:07:20,916
[RYU] Granite Blast.

156
00:07:30,125 --> 00:07:31,458
[YUTA] Ishigori?

157
00:07:31,708 --> 00:07:33,541
[TAKAKO]
It came from that rooftop.

158
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:35,208
Too close for comfort.

159
00:07:35,708 --> 00:07:37,916
[YUTA]
Even with Rika
protecting the stadium,

160
00:07:38,125 --> 00:07:40,541
a direct hit from an attack
on that level

161
00:07:40,750 --> 00:07:42,291
will leave several people dead.

162
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:44,833
So I have to take
Ishigori out first.

163
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:47,208
[TAKAKO]
Now that Kurourushi
and Dhruv are gone,

164
00:07:47,416 --> 00:07:50,041
I have no reason
to let Ishigori run free.

165
00:07:50,250 --> 00:07:51,875
I'll take both him
and Okkotsu...

166
00:07:52,083 --> 00:07:53,166
-[YUTA]
Now.
-[TAKAKO]
...out.

167
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:56,708
[RYU] Granite Blast!

168
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:10,833
Come on.

169
00:08:11,041 --> 00:08:12,833
Don't disappoint me.

170
00:08:14,541 --> 00:08:15,791
He's gone?

171
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:18,708
No. That's where Okkotsu
dug a hole earlier.

172
00:08:23,583 --> 00:08:24,791
Can't you fight

173
00:08:24,791 --> 00:08:26,166
without blowing up
everything around you?

174
00:08:26,458 --> 00:08:30,333
Oh, but that won't satisfy
my hunger, Okkotsu.

175
00:08:31,583 --> 00:08:33,291
JUJUTSU KAISEN

176
00:08:34,541 --> 00:08:37,875
Would you tell a starving kid
with a feast in front of him

177
00:08:38,083 --> 00:08:40,458
to take his time and eat slower?

178
00:08:41,875 --> 00:08:43,166
[YUTA] Wouldn't anyone?

179
00:08:44,583 --> 00:08:45,708
[RYU] I guess so.

180
00:08:45,916 --> 00:08:47,125
Most probably would.

181
00:08:47,333 --> 00:08:48,833
That was a bad example.

182
00:08:49,541 --> 00:08:53,625
My first run at life wasn't
completely lacking flavor.

183
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:56,958
Some of the guys I fought
had real backbone.

184
00:08:57,166 --> 00:08:59,333
I even met a nice woman, too.

185
00:08:59,541 --> 00:09:02,916
Frankly, it'd be hard to say
I had any regrets at all.

186
00:09:05,291 --> 00:09:07,750
This vague hunger
I constantly feel

187
00:09:07,958 --> 00:09:10,625
is always gnawing
at me, Okkotsu.

188
00:09:10,833 --> 00:09:14,416
Everyone's always wondering
what I'm so unsatisfied about.

189
00:09:16,041 --> 00:09:19,708
These cigarettes have
a slightly sweet aftertaste.

190
00:09:21,416 --> 00:09:22,708
You know what it was?

191
00:09:23,166 --> 00:09:25,291
There was no dessert in my life.

192
00:09:26,416 --> 00:09:27,500
[YUTA]
Here it comes.

193
00:09:27,708 --> 00:09:28,833
[thuds]

194
00:09:31,666 --> 00:09:32,666
[laughs]

195
00:09:32,875 --> 00:09:33,916
[punching]

196
00:09:35,750 --> 00:09:38,125
[RYU]
Why am I unsatisfied?

197
00:09:38,541 --> 00:09:40,458
I think you know!

198
00:09:44,166 --> 00:09:45,541
-[gasps]
-[chuckles]

199
00:09:47,291 --> 00:09:48,250
[groans]

200
00:09:48,458 --> 00:09:49,875
[RYU]
I'm unsatisfied

201
00:09:50,083 --> 00:09:51,916
because I'm not fulfilled!

202
00:09:55,041 --> 00:09:56,125
[grunts]

203
00:09:56,458 --> 00:09:57,500
[Ryu grunts]

204
00:10:02,333 --> 00:10:03,333
[gasps]

205
00:10:05,416 --> 00:10:07,250
You'd better not be crushed.

206
00:10:09,125 --> 00:10:10,208
[grunts]

207
00:10:14,625 --> 00:10:15,833
[choking]

208
00:10:16,666 --> 00:10:18,291
[grunting]

209
00:10:19,708 --> 00:10:20,916
[grunts]

210
00:10:22,041 --> 00:10:23,125
[grunts]

211
00:10:24,125 --> 00:10:25,833
[RYU] Hey, watch the hair.

212
00:10:30,375 --> 00:10:31,416
[grunts]

213
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:43,833
[YUTA]
Nice.

214
00:10:49,541 --> 00:10:52,458
[Ryu grunts]
Not calling your shikigami?

215
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:55,333
I can't right now.

216
00:10:55,875 --> 00:10:57,833
Not with you going wild.

217
00:10:58,041 --> 00:10:59,916
[RYU] Oh, that's a shame.

218
00:11:00,875 --> 00:11:02,375
[running]

219
00:11:03,083 --> 00:11:05,208
[YUTA]
He's probably
trying to limit where I can go.

220
00:11:06,166 --> 00:11:07,458
But I'll break through...

221
00:11:08,875 --> 00:11:10,208
head
-
on!

222
00:11:11,416 --> 00:11:12,875
Sweet!

223
00:11:13,083 --> 00:11:14,458
That's it, Okkotsu!

224
00:11:14,833 --> 00:11:16,375
Keep on coming!

225
00:11:18,666 --> 00:11:21,083
[YUTA]
His cursed energy,
so precise!

226
00:11:26,833 --> 00:11:28,666
-Here's your reward!
-[gasps]

227
00:11:32,666 --> 00:11:33,833
Uh-oh.

228
00:11:34,375 --> 00:11:36,500
I overheated my hair.

229
00:11:36,708 --> 00:11:37,500
[creaks]

230
00:11:37,708 --> 00:11:38,625
[crashes]

231
00:11:42,916 --> 00:11:44,041
[grunts]

232
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:46,708
[RYU]
You're good, Okkotsu.

233
00:11:47,125 --> 00:11:48,791
Could you be the one?

234
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,500
Are you my dessert?

235
00:11:54,166 --> 00:11:55,208
[Yuta grunts]

236
00:11:57,416 --> 00:11:58,750
You're great!

237
00:11:58,958 --> 00:12:01,541
Best I've seen so far!

238
00:12:05,666 --> 00:12:07,500
[TAKAKO]
What I strike isn't the person,

239
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,958
but the surface of the sky.

240
00:12:10,166 --> 00:12:11,041
[shatters]

241
00:12:11,708 --> 00:12:13,208
Thin Ice Breaker!

242
00:12:16,291 --> 00:12:18,916
Get lost, you pile of vomit!

243
00:12:21,750 --> 00:12:23,416
Shut your mouth,

244
00:12:23,625 --> 00:12:25,458
-dick cheese!
-[gasps]

245
00:12:27,333 --> 00:12:28,500
[chuckles]

246
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:32,583
This guy's resilient.

247
00:12:32,791 --> 00:12:34,125
Glad you're alive.

248
00:12:34,333 --> 00:12:36,208
I wanted to torment you
some more.

249
00:12:36,875 --> 00:12:39,083
[groans] What a hit.

250
00:12:39,291 --> 00:12:40,666
That was the first time
I've been forced

251
00:12:40,875 --> 00:12:42,291
to eat my own technique.

252
00:12:42,958 --> 00:12:45,625
Reverse cursed technique
is a pain to deal with,

253
00:12:45,833 --> 00:12:48,250
but it burns cursed energy
like crazy.

254
00:12:50,208 --> 00:12:53,916
We're finally seeing the bottom
of your reserves, Okkotsu.

255
00:12:54,208 --> 00:12:56,791
No matter how high
-
end
the sweet shop is,

256
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,541
seeing the displays empty
at closing time

257
00:12:59,750 --> 00:13:01,750
is always disappointing.

258
00:13:02,458 --> 00:13:03,625
Guess it wasn't you.

259
00:13:03,833 --> 00:13:06,708
[panting]

260
00:13:09,791 --> 00:13:11,250
[YUTA]
I wanted
to gain more distance

261
00:13:11,458 --> 00:13:13,000
from everyone in the stadium,

262
00:13:13,208 --> 00:13:14,958
keep them out of harm's way.

263
00:13:15,166 --> 00:13:16,166
Oh, well.

264
00:13:20,583 --> 00:13:22,500
Come to me, Rika.

265
00:13:23,250 --> 00:13:24,833
Give me everything!

266
00:13:25,458 --> 00:13:26,833
[both gasp]

267
00:13:27,375 --> 00:13:30,041
[TAKAKO]
His shikigami
completely manifested?

268
00:13:30,250 --> 00:13:31,625
[RYU]
How does that work?

269
00:13:31,625 --> 00:13:34,083
And he's swelling
with cursed energy again!

270
00:13:34,916 --> 00:13:37,583
[RIKA]
Which would you like, Yuta?

271
00:13:38,416 --> 00:13:39,583
Thank you.

272
00:13:39,791 --> 00:13:40,833
I'll take that one.

273
00:13:41,458 --> 00:13:42,916
[chuckles]

274
00:13:42,916 --> 00:13:45,250
[NARRATOR]
Rika is
the stockpile of cursed energy

275
00:13:45,458 --> 00:13:48,000
and the externalization
of Okkotsu's technique
.

276
00:13:48,208 --> 00:13:51,166
It remained with him
after Rika Orimoto passed on.

277
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:53,541
While connected to Rika
through the ring,

278
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:55,041
he gains the following.

279
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:56,750
Use of his cursed technique,

280
00:13:56,958 --> 00:13:58,833
the complete manifestation
of Rika,

281
00:13:59,041 --> 00:14:01,291
and the cursed energy
supplied by Rika.

282
00:14:02,041 --> 00:14:04,458
Yuta can remain
connected to Rika

283
00:14:04,666 --> 00:14:06,083
for five minutes.

284
00:14:08,333 --> 00:14:09,375
[YUTA] Okay.

285
00:14:09,916 --> 00:14:11,250
Let's go.

286
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,958
[TAKAKO]
Don't
underestimate me.
[gasps]

287
00:14:16,916 --> 00:14:17,875
[Yuta hisses]

288
00:14:18,166 --> 00:14:19,500
[YUTA]
Don't move.

289
00:14:19,916 --> 00:14:21,583
[TAKAKO]
Snake eyes and fangs.

290
00:14:21,791 --> 00:14:23,166
I can't move.

291
00:14:24,833 --> 00:14:26,041
[punching]

292
00:14:26,250 --> 00:14:27,541
[Takako groaning]

293
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,375
Oh, man.

294
00:14:29,583 --> 00:14:31,250
You are super sweet, huh?

295
00:14:31,625 --> 00:14:33,041
[Takako groaning]

296
00:14:33,875 --> 00:14:34,875
[YUTA] Rika.

297
00:14:35,083 --> 00:14:36,375
-[RIKA] Right!
-[RYU] Yeah!

298
00:14:37,625 --> 00:14:38,708
[RYU]
Oh, no!

299
00:14:38,916 --> 00:14:39,791
[thuds]

300
00:14:40,833 --> 00:14:42,000
[strains]

301
00:14:44,416 --> 00:14:46,166
That was close! Huh?

302
00:14:46,791 --> 00:14:49,916
[grunts] You can't
get rid of me that easy!

303
00:14:50,125 --> 00:14:51,958
♪

304
00:15:06,583 --> 00:15:07,541
[Takako grunts]

305
00:15:07,750 --> 00:15:09,375
-[Ryu groans]
-[gasps]

306
00:15:15,041 --> 00:15:16,083
[Yuta groans]

307
00:15:16,750 --> 00:15:17,791
[Rika gasps]

308
00:15:18,125 --> 00:15:19,291
[hisses]

309
00:15:19,500 --> 00:15:20,541
[RIKA] You!

310
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:22,916
You hurt Yuta!

311
00:15:24,083 --> 00:15:25,083
[Takako gasps]

312
00:15:25,291 --> 00:15:26,125
[grunts]

313
00:15:29,958 --> 00:15:31,000
[gasps]

314
00:15:31,833 --> 00:15:33,458
[whooshing]

315
00:15:33,666 --> 00:15:35,000
[YUTA]
What now?

316
00:15:35,708 --> 00:15:36,958
[RYU] Let's go!

317
00:15:37,166 --> 00:15:38,166
[Yuta grunts]

318
00:15:39,291 --> 00:15:40,666
[laughs]

319
00:15:40,666 --> 00:15:43,416
[YUTA]
Even with this,
I can't fully block it.

320
00:15:46,500 --> 00:15:48,416
-Wanna go?
-[grunts]

321
00:15:53,625 --> 00:15:54,666
[Rika grunts]

322
00:16:05,375 --> 00:16:06,416
[gasps]

323
00:16:10,458 --> 00:16:11,875
[Takako grunts]

324
00:16:12,083 --> 00:16:13,291
[growls]

325
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:14,333
[cracks]

326
00:16:14,541 --> 00:16:15,416
[gasps]

327
00:16:16,750 --> 00:16:18,833
[TAKAKO] Thin Ice Breaker!

328
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:29,125
[scoffs]

329
00:16:29,125 --> 00:16:30,583
The Sun, Moon, and Stars Squad
was Fujiwara Clan's assassins.

330
00:16:30,583 --> 00:16:31,958
We lived in darkness and served
with selfless devotion.

331
00:16:31,958 --> 00:16:33,041
We were even forbidden
from having our own names.

332
00:16:33,041 --> 00:16:33,958
Yet that man
once granted me a name.

333
00:16:33,958 --> 00:16:35,083
So he could execute me instead

334
00:16:35,083 --> 00:16:35,791
for his crime
of slaying his own kin.

335
00:16:36,083 --> 00:16:38,958
[scoffs] Fujiwara!

336
00:16:39,291 --> 00:16:42,000
[RYU] I've still got
a strong appetite!

337
00:16:42,375 --> 00:16:44,250
[growls]

338
00:16:44,458 --> 00:16:46,416
Let's keep chowing down!

339
00:16:48,083 --> 00:16:50,375
[TAKAKO]
It's always you, Fujiwara!

340
00:16:50,583 --> 00:16:52,375
You're always getting in my way!

341
00:16:52,750 --> 00:16:54,458
Are you that afraid of me?

342
00:16:54,666 --> 00:16:57,166
Afraid of me
becoming my own person?

343
00:16:57,375 --> 00:16:59,750
-[hisses]
-[grunts]

344
00:17:02,791 --> 00:17:05,666
[NARRATOR]
Okkotsu
defeated Dhruv Lakdawalla,

345
00:17:06,333 --> 00:17:09,250
whose technique made
the path of his shikigami

346
00:17:09,458 --> 00:17:10,625
into his domain,

347
00:17:10,625 --> 00:17:14,166
which cut into anything
it touched.

348
00:17:14,458 --> 00:17:15,416
[slashes]

349
00:17:15,625 --> 00:17:16,750
[gasps]

350
00:17:17,458 --> 00:17:19,875
[TAKAKO]
This is Dhruv's technique.

351
00:17:20,958 --> 00:17:22,041
Does that mean

352
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:25,291
Okkotsu's technique is Copy?

353
00:17:26,250 --> 00:17:28,041
[Yuta grunting]

354
00:17:28,250 --> 00:17:29,458
[Takako grunting]

355
00:17:31,208 --> 00:17:33,041
[Ryu grunting]

356
00:17:34,458 --> 00:17:35,875
[punching]

357
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:40,458
[YUTA] I don't know
what my ancestors did to you,

358
00:17:40,666 --> 00:17:42,666
but that has nothing
to do with me.

359
00:17:42,875 --> 00:17:44,541
If you live only
for your own sake,

360
00:17:44,750 --> 00:17:46,541
you're eventually
going to reach your limit.

361
00:17:46,750 --> 00:17:47,708
[TAKAKO] Shut up!

362
00:17:47,916 --> 00:17:49,833
Live for the sake of others?

363
00:17:50,041 --> 00:17:52,125
You think I'll eventually
reach my limit?

364
00:17:53,583 --> 00:17:55,958
Stop barking those things at me!

365
00:17:56,166 --> 00:17:58,666
It's easy for you to say.
You've already become someone!

366
00:17:58,875 --> 00:17:59,791
[snickers]

367
00:18:03,500 --> 00:18:04,666
[grunts]

368
00:18:05,750 --> 00:18:07,375
[♪ tense music playing]

369
00:18:14,166 --> 00:18:15,666
[RYU] Quit your whining!

370
00:18:16,041 --> 00:18:17,875
Because at this point,

371
00:18:19,041 --> 00:18:21,916
words are meaningless!

372
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:28,333
[ALL] Domain Expansion!

373
00:18:30,708 --> 00:18:33,166
Yuta! Give him back!

374
00:18:33,708 --> 00:18:36,500
[TAKAKO]
Even if it tries
to penetrate the barrier later.

375
00:18:36,708 --> 00:18:38,166
[RYU]
I ain't gonna drag this out!

376
00:18:38,375 --> 00:18:40,541
Let's settle this,
nice and sweet!

377
00:18:42,916 --> 00:18:44,250
[NARRATOR]
At that moment,

378
00:18:44,458 --> 00:18:46,875
the black devil
of the modern age...

379
00:18:47,083 --> 00:18:48,833
[KUROURUSHI]
I told you,

380
00:18:49,041 --> 00:18:51,583
I like the taste of iron!

381
00:18:51,958 --> 00:18:54,041
[NARRATOR]
...flew into the barriers.

382
00:18:55,041 --> 00:18:56,541
[all gasp]

383
00:18:56,541 --> 00:18:59,416
[NARRATOR]
Kurourushi
had completed parthenogenesis

384
00:18:59,625 --> 00:19:01,083
before going dormant.

385
00:19:02,458 --> 00:19:05,083
So Kurourushi
was still alive and well

386
00:19:05,291 --> 00:19:06,416
as a cursed spirit.

387
00:19:06,833 --> 00:19:08,791
The complex forces
of their domains

388
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:11,625
had been keeping
the three sorcerers in check.

389
00:19:11,833 --> 00:19:13,250
But this intruder

390
00:19:13,458 --> 00:19:14,833
was unexpected.

391
00:19:15,333 --> 00:19:17,375
And so the barriers...

392
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:21,416
collapsed.

393
00:19:26,625 --> 00:19:28,625
[TAKAKO]
How's Kurourushi still alive?

394
00:19:28,833 --> 00:19:29,875
-[Yuta grunts]
-[Takako gasps]

395
00:19:32,166 --> 00:19:33,875
-[grunts]
-[shatters]

396
00:19:34,083 --> 00:19:35,791
[TAKAKO]
Damn!
I can't use my technique

397
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:37,666
right after Domain Expansion.

398
00:19:37,875 --> 00:19:39,125
-[Kurourushi growls]
-[Takako gasps]

399
00:19:40,625 --> 00:19:44,541
[Rika chomping]

400
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:46,500
How dare you take my arm!

401
00:19:46,708 --> 00:19:49,291
-Fujiwara!
-[RYU] Enough, Uro.

402
00:19:49,500 --> 00:19:50,875
Quiet.

403
00:19:51,375 --> 00:19:54,541
You and the roach were
never invited to my table.

404
00:19:56,125 --> 00:19:57,791
Granite Blast.

405
00:19:58,000 --> 00:19:59,625
[explosion]

406
00:20:01,208 --> 00:20:04,791
[NARRATOR]
Ishigori's technique
is Cursed Energy Discharge.

407
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:07,166
It's an extremely simple attack,

408
00:20:07,375 --> 00:20:09,291
but it performs just as well
,

409
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:12,666
even when his technique
is burnt out.

410
00:20:13,625 --> 00:20:15,041
[Kurourushi growling]

411
00:20:20,791 --> 00:20:21,958
Now.

412
00:20:25,041 --> 00:20:27,125
Welcome to my table...

413
00:20:28,500 --> 00:20:29,625
Okkotsu.

414
00:20:30,750 --> 00:20:34,208
-Rika, let's go.
-[growls]

415
00:20:37,291 --> 00:20:41,000
[NARRATOR]
Okkotsu can discharge
a high volume of cursed energy,

416
00:20:41,208 --> 00:20:44,125
but only while Rika
is completely manifested.

417
00:20:44,333 --> 00:20:47,916
However, his maximum output
is slightly inferior

418
00:20:48,125 --> 00:20:49,666
to Ishigori's.

419
00:20:49,666 --> 00:20:52,458
So he planned to charge
and unleash his cursed energy

420
00:20:52,666 --> 00:20:55,500
before Ishigori
reached maximum output.

421
00:20:55,708 --> 00:20:58,083
-
[Yuta gasps]
-
But he changed his mind.

422
00:20:58,791 --> 00:21:01,458
LET'S LET IT ALL OUT!

423
00:21:01,666 --> 00:21:04,000
400 years of longing.

424
00:21:04,458 --> 00:21:07,416
The intense gaze
full of that hunger

425
00:21:07,625 --> 00:21:10,000
melted Yuta Okkotsu's heart,

426
00:21:10,375 --> 00:21:13,500
even though he would
likely never find meaning

427
00:21:13,708 --> 00:21:14,958
in fighting.

428
00:21:16,541 --> 00:21:18,333
All right, just this once.

429
00:21:20,208 --> 00:21:22,125
♪

430
00:21:25,750 --> 00:21:26,708
[both grunt]

431
00:21:26,916 --> 00:21:28,541
[♪ theme song playing]

432
00:21:37,083 --> 00:21:40,625
That was some
seriously sweet stuff, Okkotsu!

433
00:21:42,666 --> 00:21:43,750
[Yuta grunts]

434
00:21:50,833 --> 00:21:52,375
Yeah, attaboy!

435
00:21:52,583 --> 00:21:55,166
Let's keep
this dinner party going!

436
00:21:58,208 --> 00:22:00,500
That big thing
can fire on its own?

437
00:22:01,291 --> 00:22:02,375
But...

438
00:22:03,250 --> 00:22:05,041
its force is weak!

439
00:22:06,583 --> 00:22:09,458
After Domain Expansion
and a meal with me,

440
00:22:09,791 --> 00:22:12,000
even you haven't had
enough time to digest

441
00:22:12,208 --> 00:22:14,000
and recover your full strength.

442
00:22:15,291 --> 00:22:16,875
I'll end this!

443
00:22:17,083 --> 00:22:19,583
Granite Blast!

444
00:22:21,333 --> 00:22:23,833
♪

445
00:22:24,041 --> 00:22:25,708
[NARRATOR]
But Okkotsu's technique...

446
00:22:27,375 --> 00:22:29,375
had already recovered.

447
00:22:30,333 --> 00:22:31,458
[Ryu gasps]

448
00:22:32,125 --> 00:22:34,000
[RYU]
He's using Uro's technique!

449
00:22:34,791 --> 00:22:37,541
I knew he was more than just
a cursed speech user.

450
00:22:37,916 --> 00:22:39,333
And I figured that big thing

451
00:22:39,541 --> 00:22:40,625
probably had
a different technique

452
00:22:40,833 --> 00:22:41,875
from Okkotsu's, too.

453
00:22:42,208 --> 00:22:43,541
So that's it!

454
00:22:43,750 --> 00:22:45,500
Okkotsu's technique is Copy!

455
00:22:45,791 --> 00:22:48,000
But there should be
strenuous conditions on it.

456
00:22:48,208 --> 00:22:49,875
When did he satisfy
those conditions?

457
00:22:50,083 --> 00:22:50,875
While I wasn't looking?

458
00:22:51,083 --> 00:22:52,500
Maybe there aren't any!

459
00:22:53,208 --> 00:22:54,375
[Yuta grunts]

460
00:22:57,250 --> 00:22:58,666
[RYU]
That was when he did it!

461
00:22:59,208 --> 00:23:00,458
[YUTA] Thin Ice Breaker!

462
00:23:02,500 --> 00:23:03,458
[Ryu groans]

463
00:23:03,458 --> 00:23:05,083
-[Rika growls]
-[Yuta grunts]

464
00:23:10,041 --> 00:23:11,375
[beeps]

465
00:23:11,958 --> 00:23:13,250
[NARRATOR]
Five minutes.

466
00:23:13,500 --> 00:23:16,916
Okkotsu's connection
to Rika was severed.

467
00:23:17,333 --> 00:23:19,125
-[growls]
-[Yuta gasps]

468
00:23:23,083 --> 00:23:24,541
[RIKA] Yuta!

469
00:23:26,416 --> 00:23:27,458
[Yuta grunts]

470
00:23:28,375 --> 00:23:30,083
[RYU]
Is this the feeling?

471
00:23:30,291 --> 00:23:31,250
[Yuta groans]

472
00:23:32,375 --> 00:23:33,708
[grunts]

473
00:23:33,916 --> 00:23:36,875
[RYU]
There's still more
after going all out!

474
00:23:37,083 --> 00:23:39,500
♪

475
00:23:40,041 --> 00:23:41,458
This is what it's like

476
00:23:41,833 --> 00:23:43,583
to eat dessert!

477
00:23:58,875 --> 00:24:00,333
[chuckles, grunts]

478
00:24:04,333 --> 00:24:05,375
[grunts]

479
00:24:05,666 --> 00:24:06,916
[YUTA] We're done.

480
00:24:10,583 --> 00:24:11,708
[RYU]
What?

481
00:24:12,166 --> 00:24:13,458
What does he mean?

482
00:24:13,833 --> 00:24:14,708
[gasps]

483
00:24:14,916 --> 00:24:17,333
♪

484
00:24:27,041 --> 00:24:29,500
[panting]

485
00:24:30,583 --> 00:24:33,250
Was that my technique?

486
00:24:35,791 --> 00:24:37,083
I see.

487
00:24:37,291 --> 00:24:39,166
He sent it sailing back to me

488
00:24:39,375 --> 00:24:41,500
using Uro's technique.

489
00:24:44,583 --> 00:24:46,250
Thank you, Okkotsu.

490
00:24:46,625 --> 00:24:47,708
[cutlery clinks]

491
00:24:52,875 --> 00:24:54,833
I'm full now.

492
00:24:55,041 --> 00:24:55,958
[chuckles]

493
00:24:58,208 --> 00:24:59,458
[thuds]

494
00:25:05,833 --> 00:25:07,125
[gasps]

495
00:25:10,250 --> 00:25:11,291
[sighs]

496
00:25:12,750 --> 00:25:15,541
Okkotsu, you're too soft.

497
00:25:15,750 --> 00:25:17,250
That's not a compliment.

498
00:25:17,458 --> 00:25:20,041
Sparing the life of a sorcerer
who fought to kill you--

499
00:25:20,250 --> 00:25:22,291
[YUTA] There's nothing
to gain from killing you.

500
00:25:22,500 --> 00:25:24,000
Uro told me the same thing.

501
00:25:24,666 --> 00:25:27,166
[RYU] You mean
that woman's still alive?

502
00:25:28,250 --> 00:25:30,708
Well, I guess
my blast was weaker

503
00:25:30,916 --> 00:25:32,791
after my Domain Expansion.

504
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:35,583
Hey, what was it
she kept going on about?

505
00:25:36,083 --> 00:25:37,583
Were you having a lovers' spat?

506
00:25:37,791 --> 00:25:39,458
Yeah, something like that.

507
00:25:39,875 --> 00:25:41,625
Eh, don't let her get to ya.

508
00:25:41,833 --> 00:25:43,583
[YUTA] There's nothing
I can say to that woman

509
00:25:43,791 --> 00:25:45,000
to change her mind.

510
00:25:45,458 --> 00:25:48,166
Anything I do say
will lead to violence.

511
00:25:48,791 --> 00:25:51,750
You see,
it's because I'm blessed.

512
00:25:51,958 --> 00:25:53,666
[Ryu sighs]
Is that how it works?

513
00:25:53,875 --> 00:25:55,416
Because frankly, I don't get it.

514
00:25:55,875 --> 00:25:58,583
[Yuta sighs] Well, regardless,

515
00:25:59,291 --> 00:26:00,541
can I have your points?

516
00:26:00,750 --> 00:26:01,625
Huh?

517
00:26:03,333 --> 00:26:04,791
Now I get it.

518
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:06,750
So if we didn't
give you our points,

519
00:26:06,958 --> 00:26:08,291
you would have killed us, right?

520
00:26:08,958 --> 00:26:12,250
[Yuta grunts]
I'm not so sure about that.

521
00:26:14,541 --> 00:26:15,791
[chuckles] All I know is

522
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:17,916
you should be grateful
to my friends.

523
00:26:20,833 --> 00:26:24,125
THROUGH THE TRANSFER
OF RYU AND TAKAKO'S POINTS,

524
00:26:24,333 --> 00:26:26,958
YUTA OKKOTSU
CAME TO POSSESS 190 POINTS.

525
00:26:28,208 --> 00:26:29,708
[♪ melancholic music playing]

526
00:26:29,916 --> 00:26:32,416
[TAKAKO]
You're the one
who's going to reach your limit.

527
00:26:36,166 --> 00:26:37,500
I've seen it.

528
00:26:41,666 --> 00:26:44,458
Be it sorcerer or cursed spirit,

529
00:26:44,708 --> 00:26:48,416
all are driven over the edge
by the same thing.

530
00:26:48,625 --> 00:26:50,041
Overwhelming aggression

531
00:26:50,250 --> 00:26:53,250
that blinds them
to everything else.

532
00:26:53,458 --> 00:26:55,041
Like a calamity.

533
00:27:00,083 --> 00:27:03,125
TO BE CONTINUED

534
00:27:03,583 --> 00:27:05,750
[♪ closing theme song playing]
